o
> approach biostatistical input as she moves forward.
>
> Dr. Wei, Dr. Francois Collin is a Berkeley-based consulting
> biostatistician who has deep experience on most diagnostic test types, in
> particular molecular tests.  He knows PCR, NGS (for RNA and DNA) of
> essentially every type.  As I mentioned in our brief discussion, Francois
> is expert at accounting for and controlling for sources of variability in
> complex molecular tests.  These variables, all the way from specimen
> collection to result generation, ultimately define the sensitivity,
> specificity and reproducibility performance of these tests.
>
> He and I are both strong believers in using biostatistical insight early
> in test design and development for the most efficient pathway to a high
> quality outcome in the end.
